§7§oNormally, when working with patterns for 'normal' recipes, you just need one interface.
To encode these recipes, you need two blocks! 

The unpackager is the second! You should put your second package recipe holder in here!

Make sure each packager/unpackager pair contains recipe holders that are identical!

The unpackager works like an interface, where it will automate the recipe using the machines directly adjacent to it!
